1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:01,710
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,710 --> 00:00:03,380
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,380 --> 00:00:04,940
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,540 --> 00:00:07,780
Why are you calling again?

5
00:00:08,350 --> 00:00:10,950
The stock deal is dead,
so why pay hush money?

6
00:00:11,650 --> 00:00:13,280
That's enough.
Stop bothering me with these calls.

7
00:00:16,390 --> 00:00:18,320
- What the...
- My gosh.

8
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:19,620
I'm so sorry.

9
00:00:19,690 --> 00:00:20,730
Seriously.

10
00:00:21,590 --> 00:00:22,790
Ms. Oh?

11
00:00:25,330 --> 00:00:28,900
We briefly met when you came
to see Ms. Choi.

12
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:32,040
I'm Chloe,
a consultant in the bio division.

13
00:00:33,370 --> 00:00:36,210
Right. The one Kim Myung Hui hired.

14
00:00:37,110 --> 00:00:38,110
Yes.

15
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:42,050
Oh no, I've stained your clothes.
I'm so sorry.

16
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:44,550
Let me get that for you.

17
00:00:44,950 --> 00:00:47,150
Wait, what are you doing?

18
00:00:50,820 --> 00:00:52,220
I said it's fine.

19
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:56,190
I'm so sorry. How clumsy of me.

20
00:00:57,030 --> 00:00:58,460
You should wash your hands.

21
00:00:59,130 --> 00:01:00,130
Unbelievable.

22
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:08,210
I guess I was just really nervous
being around you.

23
00:01:09,010 --> 00:01:11,280
I'm not usually this nervous,
even around President Kim.

24
00:01:11,910 --> 00:01:13,980
You just have
such a strong presence.

25
00:01:17,150 --> 00:01:18,880
A strong presence?

26
00:01:20,420 --> 00:01:23,320
You mean something like charisma?

27
00:01:23,660 --> 00:01:27,090
Exactly. You seemed extraordinary
from the moment I saw you.

28
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:28,790
Of course.

29
00:01:29,530 --> 00:01:31,500
I hear you're good at what you do.
You've got a good eye.

30
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:45,480
Hold on.

31
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,600
Funny...

32
00:02:09,570 --> 00:02:11,140
You still haven't said
how you'll make it up to me.

33
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:16,440
You don't think flattery gets you
off the hook, do you?

34
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,610
Of course not.

35
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:20,450
You can bill me
for the dry cleaning or...

36
00:02:20,450 --> 00:02:21,450
Dry cleaning?

37
00:02:21,980 --> 00:02:24,420
Do I look like I can't pay
for my own dry cleaning?

38
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:28,790
I heard you were a hotshot overseas.

39
00:02:29,390 --> 00:02:31,490
Get me a designer piece
that's not available in Korea yet.

40
00:02:32,490 --> 00:02:33,490
That shouldn't be so hard.

41
00:02:34,990 --> 00:02:37,200
Yes, of course.
I'll have it ready for you.

42
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:41,300
What?

43
00:02:42,170 --> 00:02:43,640
What's going on?

44
00:02:43,870 --> 00:02:46,970
I think it's a blackout.
We should leave since it's not safe.

45
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:54,110
I'll be on my way then.

46
00:02:54,380 --> 00:02:55,950
It was a pleasure meeting you.

47
00:03:08,060 --> 00:03:09,060
Wait, my phone.

48
00:03:18,570 --> 00:03:19,570
What's this?

49
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:22,210
(Out of service,
Please check back shortly.)

50
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,950
Is anyone there?
Open this door right now!

51
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:29,780
Over here!

52
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:35,620
Didn't the lights go out
at the perfect time?

53
00:03:36,390 --> 00:03:38,960
Yes. Thanks to you,
I got out of a tight spot.

54
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:40,930
I locked the door,

55
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,860
so it'll take her a while.

56
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:49,470
If she kidnapped someone
and held him captive,

57
00:03:49,730 --> 00:03:51,900
she must've had help.

58
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:56,710
Let's track her communications
and see who contacts her.

59
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:16,930
We'll figure this out.

60
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:21,730
The false accusation,
this forced marriage,

61
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,340
and any hardships we face
in this family.

62
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,080
Thank you, my son.

63
00:04:47,590 --> 00:04:50,860
They say even the toughest hikes
give you a chance to rest.

64
00:04:51,830 --> 00:04:55,930
Though this case is a headache,
you managed to talk to Min Jun...

65
00:04:56,330 --> 00:04:58,200
and clear the air.

66
00:04:58,870 --> 00:05:01,440
I hope you two can be as close
as you used to be.

67
00:05:03,070 --> 00:05:05,140
When I first held Min Jun
as a newborn...

68
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:08,380
and became part of the Adele family,

69
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:14,950
he held on to me
with his tiny little hand.

70
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:18,090
It was as though
he were telling me...

71
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:20,590
we'd be okay,
as long as we had each other.

72
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:25,130
I felt the same way yesterday.

73
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:29,230
Just incredibly grateful and sorry.

74
00:05:37,310 --> 00:05:40,310
Now I need to act,
for Min Jun's sake.

75
00:05:41,650 --> 00:05:44,680
But you still haven't found
the person they're holding.

76
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:47,020
Don't you need him to testify?

77
00:05:48,990 --> 00:05:53,290
I'll make Yu Na and Oh Jung Ran
confess to their own crimes...

78
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,660
right in front of Chairman Park.

79
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,320
(Driver Song)

80
00:06:19,620 --> 00:06:22,320
Jung Ran, this is just wrong.

81
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:28,330
You made me a promise.

82
00:06:28,690 --> 00:06:30,360
You promised to hold him
for a few days,

83
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:32,830
keep him quiet, and let him go.

84
00:06:37,070 --> 00:06:39,400
And now you're going
to sell him off overseas...

85
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,640
to avoid paying him?

86
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:44,910
Chairman Park didn't order this.
Why do you have to go this far?

87
00:06:45,210 --> 00:06:47,110
Let's just pay him,

88
00:06:47,310 --> 00:06:51,080
make sure he keeps his mouth shut,
and let him go. Okay?

89
00:06:54,990 --> 00:06:57,420
Say something, Jung Ran!

90
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:04,500
Oh Jung Ran.

91
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:07,030
She's a truly terrifying woman.

92
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:11,670
If we don't hurry,
she'll really send him overseas.

93
00:07:30,190 --> 00:07:31,360
Don't tell me...

94
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:34,730
she came because she knows
what Yu Na did.

95
00:07:37,330 --> 00:07:39,800
Goodness, the tension is killing me.

96
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:43,800
Why is she just sipping her tea
and not saying a word?

97
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:50,680
Thank you for your help
the other day.

98
00:07:52,010 --> 00:07:55,280
We kept the shares,
and we have you to thank for it.

99
00:07:56,650 --> 00:08:01,090
Anyway, did you expect us
to get on our knees and thank you?

100
00:08:01,450 --> 00:08:03,320
We're grateful,

101
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:06,860
but it's rude
to just show up unannounced.

102
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:22,670
Isn't this Yu Na's...

103
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:26,210
This was worn by the person
who stole the design book.

104
00:08:29,810 --> 00:08:32,620
I got this from an anonymous source,

105
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:36,090
and it looks just like
the jacket Ms. Choi has.

106
00:08:37,460 --> 00:08:41,330
Weren't you making a big deal
about a jacket a few days ago?

107
00:08:41,490 --> 00:08:44,400
Are you trying to make our Yu Na out
to be a thief?

108
00:08:44,660 --> 00:08:46,300
For goodness' sake.

109
00:08:46,830 --> 00:08:48,370
Our Yu Na...

110
00:08:48,370 --> 00:08:50,370
As thoughtless as she can be,

111
00:08:50,430 --> 00:08:53,670
she did try to hand over our shares,

112
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:57,170
but she's just not capable
of stealing.

113
00:08:59,110 --> 00:09:00,110
I see.

114
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:04,820
If Ms. Choi still has the jacket,
then she's not a suspect.

115
00:09:06,950 --> 00:09:09,550
That's why I'm here to confirm it.

116
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:13,960
I want to be sure
before I report to the chairman.

117
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:18,230
You're reporting this
to the chairman?

118
00:09:18,860 --> 00:09:21,630
I'm going to report to the chairman
and give the evidence to the police.

119
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:24,770
The detectives already said
they would come to the house.

120
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,240
Goodness.

121
00:09:26,940 --> 00:09:28,070
Now,

122
00:09:28,370 --> 00:09:31,910
will you please check
if Ms. Choi has her jacket?

123
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:35,280
What?

124
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:38,920
Well, that's...

125
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:42,720
I took it to the dry cleaner's.

126
00:09:43,490 --> 00:09:45,160
- The dry cleaner's?
- Yes.

127
00:09:45,820 --> 00:09:48,560
Yes, of course.
I'm sure that's the case.

128
00:09:49,830 --> 00:09:53,400
So you're saying
Ms. Choi wasn't involved?

129
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:56,130
- What?
- Of course she wasn't!

130
00:09:58,470 --> 00:09:59,500
I see.

131
00:10:00,770 --> 00:10:03,640
Very well.
I'll take your word for it...

132
00:10:03,770 --> 00:10:05,880
and report to the chairman.

133
00:10:21,690 --> 00:10:23,390
You'll be the ones...

134
00:10:23,690 --> 00:10:25,930
who make Choi Yu Na walk
right into a trap.

135
00:10:25,930 --> 00:10:26,930
Goodness.

136
00:10:32,470 --> 00:10:33,900
(Team Leader, Choi Yu Na)

137
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,970
Why haven't I heard
from Oh Jung Ran?

138
00:10:37,310 --> 00:10:38,780
Why is she so quiet about...

139
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:40,240
the stock deal I messed up?
It's unnerving.

140
00:10:41,780 --> 00:10:44,650
I can't even call her first
because she might demand the shares.

141
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:46,620
This is driving me crazy.

142
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,120
(Mom)

143
00:10:54,890 --> 00:10:55,960
What is it?

144
00:10:57,330 --> 00:10:59,160
We're in huge trouble!

145
00:11:01,430 --> 00:11:02,430
What?

146
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:05,970
Have you reviewed the videos?

147
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,840
Yes, we compared
the initial accusation video,

148
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:12,110
the CCTV footage,
and the confession video.

149
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:16,450
Their dominant hands are different,
and their builds don't match either.

150
00:11:17,010 --> 00:11:20,220
We also think
the confession video is fake.

151
00:11:20,990 --> 00:11:22,820
It's suspicious
that he's off the grid too.

152
00:11:23,850 --> 00:11:26,690
We'll look into it, keeping
kidnapping and confinement in mind.

153
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:31,000
Right. Please be discreet and quick.

154
00:11:31,330 --> 00:11:32,330
Of course.

155
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:35,830
Please update the victim, Chloe,
on the new direction of the case.

156
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:38,640
- Understood.
- We'll be leaving now.

157
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:05,160
Chloe.

158
00:12:07,330 --> 00:12:08,900
You are a precious...

159
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:11,640
and perfect person.

160
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:16,940
I'll remind you
how precious and perfect you are.

161
00:12:28,090 --> 00:12:29,090
What's up?

162
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:30,860
Got somewhere urgent to be?

163
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,720
I'm on my way to see Chloe.

164
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,560
She wasn't in her office.

165
00:12:35,390 --> 00:12:37,760
- Why are you looking for her?
- It's nothing.

166
00:12:39,260 --> 00:12:42,770
You say that,
but your face says something else.

167
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:45,740
Isn't this about
that false accusation?

168
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:48,970
Can't you fill me in
on what's been happening...

169
00:12:48,970 --> 00:12:50,670
since the confession video came out?

170
00:12:55,010 --> 00:12:56,410
You're going to keep
dodging the question?

171
00:12:58,180 --> 00:13:01,120
Do you think I'd mess things up
if I knew?

172
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,290
Or do you just not want me involved?

173
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:12,760
Tell me what's going on.

174
00:13:13,330 --> 00:13:15,270
Don't make me get serious.

175
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:19,370
What's the issue
with the false accusation case?

176
00:13:21,540 --> 00:13:22,910
He's being held captive.

177
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:27,950
Chloe.

178
00:13:28,180 --> 00:13:30,810
If we don't find him soon,
he'll be sent overseas somewhere...

179
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:33,120
that he can never come back from.

180
00:13:33,180 --> 00:13:35,290
Who's holding him captive,
and who's sending him away?

181
00:13:36,420 --> 00:13:38,560
Don't tell me Choi Yu Na
would go that far.

182
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:40,860
- It's not her, but...
- Chloe, hold on.

183
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,560
Why did you stop her?

184
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:46,060
Don't leave me
in the dark like this.

185
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:49,130
This is urgent,
and we need your help.

186
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:53,800
You need my help?

187
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:55,070
Yes.

188
00:13:55,810 --> 00:13:57,840
The one who locked him up is...

189
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,280
It's your mother.

190
00:14:20,830 --> 00:14:22,400
I thought you might need this.

191
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:35,380
To be honest,

192
00:14:37,210 --> 00:14:40,780
I always suspected she was capable
of doing terrible things.

193
00:14:43,190 --> 00:14:45,220
If our "great" chairman...

194
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:49,330
had given the job to my mother
instead of yours,

195
00:14:50,860 --> 00:14:52,500
it was never going
to be anything good, right?

196
00:14:55,670 --> 00:14:59,400
I gave her a hard time
and told her to be nice,

197
00:15:02,410 --> 00:15:04,940
but most of the time,
I wanted to take her side.

198
00:15:08,380 --> 00:15:09,450
Because the bad guy...

199
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:13,380
is our father,
the one calling the shots.

200
00:15:13,850 --> 00:15:16,920
So I figured I should cut her some slack,
since she has no choice.

201
00:15:19,990 --> 00:15:21,090
That's what I thought.

202
00:15:24,060 --> 00:15:25,230
But this?

203
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:30,200
This?

204
00:15:33,940 --> 00:15:35,440
She chose to do this herself.

205
00:15:39,510 --> 00:15:41,650
It shows
the kind of person my mother is.

206
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:47,480
You can back out if it's too much.

207
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:54,430
I kept saying...

208
00:15:55,990 --> 00:15:58,460
that Ms. Oh and I
aren't a package deal.

209
00:16:03,430 --> 00:16:05,200
I guess we were one after all.

210
00:16:06,940 --> 00:16:08,770
She's your mother. Your family.

211
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:16,080
If I back out of this,

212
00:16:17,950 --> 00:16:19,650
how could I ever look you
in the eye again?

213
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:22,650
I couldn't be cool around Chloe.

214
00:16:22,650 --> 00:16:24,590
I'd have to avoid her all the time.

215
00:16:26,190 --> 00:16:27,620
That's a pathetic way to live.

216
00:16:29,190 --> 00:16:31,030
Not my style either.

217
00:16:34,970 --> 00:16:36,530
If there's anything I can do,

218
00:16:40,940 --> 00:16:42,040
I have to at least try.

219
00:16:42,970 --> 00:16:44,410
Are you sure about this?

220
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:48,880
It'll be tough, sure.

221
00:16:49,410 --> 00:16:50,410
It'll be hard, but...

222
00:16:52,380 --> 00:16:53,750
But if you look at it another way,

223
00:16:54,690 --> 00:16:56,390
there's still a chance, right?

224
00:17:00,020 --> 00:17:02,230
I have to stop Ms. Oh...

225
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:05,960
before things get worse.

226
00:17:31,820 --> 00:17:33,090
Once again,

227
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:35,460
I used you.

228
00:17:36,730 --> 00:17:37,730
I'm so sorry.

229
00:17:48,570 --> 00:17:50,310
Don't waste your energy.

230
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:52,940
There's no use
trying to stop Jung Ran.

231
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:56,410
She's already completely lost it,
and you're as good as sold...

232
00:17:56,950 --> 00:17:58,880
to some foreign country.

233
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:04,020
You'll meet crueler people than you
and finally get what you deserve.

234
00:18:07,020 --> 00:18:09,260
You should've lived a better life.

235
00:18:09,260 --> 00:18:12,700
You reap what you sow.
There's no escaping karma.

236
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:15,430
You’ll pay for every sin you commit.

237
00:18:15,430 --> 00:18:17,330
If not you, then your kids...

238
00:18:21,810 --> 00:18:22,940
Right.

239
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:28,710
Let's be decent
and not drag our kids into this.

240
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:36,350
Hey, Hyun Jun. What's...

241
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:39,760
What? You're hurt?

242
00:18:42,090 --> 00:18:45,060
Don't tell me this is instant karma.

243
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:48,230
Where are you?

244
00:19:04,750 --> 00:19:06,420
However I look at it,
it was that witch.

245
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,950
That brat Chloe,
or whatever her name is,

246
00:19:08,950 --> 00:19:10,990
distracted me and snatched my phone.

247
00:19:12,460 --> 00:19:16,230
She teamed up with Kim Myung Hui
and pulled one over on me.

248
00:19:17,690 --> 00:19:20,560
I won't let them get away with this.

249
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:26,040
What are you doing here?
What is it? Hey!

250
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:28,340
Stop right there.

251
00:19:28,710 --> 00:19:31,680
Stop. Do you have a death wish?

252
00:19:32,340 --> 00:19:34,010
Why...

253
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,510
Why are you here?
What about that guy?

254
00:19:36,580 --> 00:19:39,880
Who cares about him right now?
Hyun Jun is hurt!

255
00:19:40,020 --> 00:19:42,020
Hyun Jun's hurt?

256
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,660
How bad is it?

257
00:19:44,660 --> 00:19:45,990
I don't know.

258
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:48,560
This is why
you should always be good.

259
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:51,700
I guess karma really does have
same-day delivery.

260
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:56,370
If anything happens to Hyun Jun,
this is on you!

261
00:19:56,430 --> 00:19:58,540
Where is he?

262
00:19:58,540 --> 00:19:59,840
- Hyun Jun.
- Goodness.

263
00:20:08,450 --> 00:20:09,950
Looks like you two came together.

264
00:20:09,950 --> 00:20:11,250
We just met outside.

265
00:20:11,580 --> 00:20:13,980
I heard you were hurt.

266
00:20:13,980 --> 00:20:16,290
Where? How? How bad is it?

267
00:20:16,350 --> 00:20:18,390
Shouldn't you see a doctor
right away?

268
00:20:18,990 --> 00:20:20,390
I don't need a doctor.

269
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:22,790
Physically, I'm fine,

270
00:20:24,290 --> 00:20:25,730
but emotionally, I'm not.

271
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:27,430
- Emotionally?
- Emotionally?

272
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,570
How should I put this?

273
00:20:30,970 --> 00:20:32,740
Who am I?

274
00:20:35,270 --> 00:20:36,670
Whose son am I?

275
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:45,650
I felt sorry for some,

276
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:48,590
ashamed of myself
in front of others,

277
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:51,560
and disappointed in someone else.

278
00:20:52,290 --> 00:20:53,960
All in one exhausting day.

279
00:20:54,790 --> 00:20:57,260
What are you talking about?

280
00:20:59,430 --> 00:21:01,200
In other words, I'm upset.

281
00:21:01,830 --> 00:21:03,730
What? What do you mean?

282
00:21:04,570 --> 00:21:06,100
I'm screaming on the inside.

283
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:10,310
Why?

284
00:21:11,070 --> 00:21:12,710
What's worrying you?

285
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:15,550
That's the question, isn't it?

286
00:21:17,550 --> 00:21:19,820
What do you suppose
I'm so worried about?

287
00:21:26,290 --> 00:21:27,460
I wonder if Ms. Oh...

288
00:21:28,730 --> 00:21:30,390
could solve it for me.

289
00:21:37,670 --> 00:21:40,570
Hold on. Hyun Jun?

290
00:21:41,670 --> 00:21:43,510
What's gotten into him?

291
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:47,740
What could be bothering him so much?
Poor Hyun Jun...

292
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:52,450
Where are you going?
He said I can help, not you.

293
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:56,620
I'll protect my own son.
You go and keep an eye on that guy.

294
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:01,260
Oh, no.

295
00:22:02,660 --> 00:22:03,890
Hyun Jun, wait!

296
00:22:07,630 --> 00:22:08,900
What is it?

297
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:11,230
What's been troubling you?

298
00:22:11,470 --> 00:22:12,570
That is the question.

299
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:15,240
I'm upset and troubled.

300
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:17,170
I get that. What's going on?

301
00:22:17,470 --> 00:22:19,210
You said I'd be able to solve it.

302
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:21,450
Ms. Oh.

303
00:22:22,310 --> 00:22:25,650
When a child does something wrong,
parents should guide them, right?

304
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:27,150
Of course.

305
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:29,790
But what about
when a parent does something wrong?

306
00:22:30,350 --> 00:22:31,350
What?

307
00:22:32,190 --> 00:22:33,220
Can children...

308
00:22:34,190 --> 00:22:35,960
guide their parents too?

309
00:22:37,460 --> 00:22:38,600
I guess.

310
00:22:41,700 --> 00:22:43,770
Did I do something to upset you?

311
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:45,300
That can't be it.

312
00:22:46,070 --> 00:22:48,940
I haven't even
been nagging you much lately.

313
00:22:50,070 --> 00:22:51,070
Ms. Oh.

314
00:22:54,910 --> 00:22:55,980
I...

315
00:22:58,950 --> 00:23:01,220
I just wish
you'd understand me, Mom.

316
00:23:03,450 --> 00:23:05,120
Seriously, what's gotten into you?

317
00:23:06,260 --> 00:23:07,720
Did you get into
some kind of trouble?

318
00:23:08,290 --> 00:23:09,930
What did you do...

319
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:11,930
to be talking like this all of a sudden?

320
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:14,970
That depends on how you look at it.

321
00:23:18,940 --> 00:23:20,500
Just remember one thing.

322
00:23:21,170 --> 00:23:22,170
I...

323
00:23:24,470 --> 00:23:26,610
worry about you a lot.

324
00:23:27,180 --> 00:23:28,180
You worry about me?

325
00:23:29,510 --> 00:23:33,180
Why have you been
so worried about me lately?

326
00:23:34,420 --> 00:23:35,420
Have you finally grown up?

327
00:23:36,890 --> 00:23:37,890
Are you ill?

328
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:52,340
I should've followed
Hyun Jun out too.

329
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:54,170
Darn.

330
00:23:54,470 --> 00:23:56,510
But now I have to go back
to that dump.

331
00:24:04,710 --> 00:24:06,620
The only way to lure Mr. Song out...

332
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:07,920
is through me.

333
00:24:09,690 --> 00:24:13,290
He goes a little overboard
whenever he thinks I'm in trouble.

334
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:15,290
He'll definitely
come looking for me.

335
00:24:16,590 --> 00:24:18,160
If you tail him,

336
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:20,560
you should be able to figure out
where they're keeping the accuser.

337
00:24:21,930 --> 00:24:23,170
That's what...

338
00:24:24,770 --> 00:24:25,800
Chloe wants, right?

339
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:40,120
What are you doing here?

340
00:24:40,450 --> 00:24:41,480
I'm coming with you.

341
00:24:43,290 --> 00:24:45,220
It's dangerous. Wait here.

342
00:24:45,390 --> 00:24:48,260
Stop being stubborn.
Come on, before we lose him.

343
00:24:55,930 --> 00:24:58,100
President Kim Myung Hui
has my jacket?

344
00:24:58,370 --> 00:25:00,300
How? I'm sure I threw it away.

345
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:02,240
What's this about an informant?

346
00:25:04,140 --> 00:25:05,180
Wait.

347
00:25:05,880 --> 00:25:06,980
Was it Chloe?

348
00:25:10,650 --> 00:25:11,650
I don't know about that.

349
00:25:12,020 --> 00:25:13,980
It seems a bit too soon
for an apology.

350
00:25:14,650 --> 00:25:18,190
There may still be more
to the story.

351
00:25:20,420 --> 00:25:22,890
Don't tell me she tailed me
to find the evidence.

352
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:25,530
That means President Kim
has my jacket.

353
00:25:27,100 --> 00:25:28,670
If the police get
their hands on that...

354
00:25:41,140 --> 00:25:43,680
Ms. Choi,
what brings you here at this hour?

355
00:25:45,520 --> 00:25:47,680
I'm here to see the chairman.

356
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:49,750
I see.

357
00:25:50,890 --> 00:25:54,260
I'll let the chairman know.
Please wait here for a moment.

358
00:26:33,060 --> 00:26:34,460
What are you mumbling about?

359
00:26:34,460 --> 00:26:36,470
Hurry. I have to go!

360
00:26:36,570 --> 00:26:37,570
To the bathroom?

361
00:26:37,970 --> 00:26:41,200
Right.
You've been tied up for hours.

362
00:26:47,310 --> 00:26:48,310
Here.

363
00:26:55,950 --> 00:26:56,950
Good.

364
00:27:01,220 --> 00:27:02,230
Who are you?

365
00:27:07,160 --> 00:27:08,670
We're not here to make friends,

366
00:27:09,030 --> 00:27:11,130
but if you want to get out of here,
follow us.

367
00:27:12,140 --> 00:27:13,170
Why should I trust you?

368
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:16,570
At least we're not trying
to smuggle you out of the country.

369
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:20,640
- Really?
- If you want to doubt us,

370
00:27:21,210 --> 00:27:22,880
do it once we're out of here.

371
00:27:24,980 --> 00:27:26,050
What?

372
00:27:26,050 --> 00:27:27,050
Hold on.

373
00:27:27,780 --> 00:27:28,790
Who are you, people?

374
00:27:30,820 --> 00:27:31,820
Darn it.

375
00:27:35,660 --> 00:27:36,660
You punk!

376
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:42,070
You!

377
00:27:42,070 --> 00:27:43,230
Min Jun!

378
00:28:06,620 --> 00:28:07,620
See?

379
00:28:08,360 --> 00:28:11,560
Like I told you,
the one who stole the design book...

380
00:28:12,030 --> 00:28:13,760
is here to destroy the evidence.

381
00:28:16,730 --> 00:28:17,800
Ms. Choi.

382
00:28:22,610 --> 00:28:23,610
Goodness.

383
00:28:27,380 --> 00:28:29,710
You've arrived just in time, Ms. Oh.

384
00:28:30,710 --> 00:28:31,980
What are you talking about?

385
00:28:33,620 --> 00:28:36,650
We've just exposed Ms. Choi's crime.

386
00:28:38,090 --> 00:28:40,460
Don't you have something to say?

387
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:43,430
What?

388
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:53,400
That's not true.

389
00:28:53,670 --> 00:28:56,140
I didn't steal the design book.

390
00:28:56,710 --> 00:28:57,710
Quiet!

391
00:29:02,250 --> 00:29:03,250
Is it true...

392
00:29:04,550 --> 00:29:06,450
you helped Ms. Choi...

393
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:09,350
in exchange for company shares?

394
00:29:10,820 --> 00:29:14,320
And you went as far as to kidnap
and imprison someone for it?

395
00:29:15,490 --> 00:29:17,160
What? No.

396
00:29:17,560 --> 00:29:18,560
It's true.

397
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:24,000
Son.

398
00:29:25,030 --> 00:29:26,040
Ms. Oh.

399
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:29,670
Mom,

400
00:29:31,310 --> 00:29:32,780
I need you to stop right here.

401
00:29:35,310 --> 00:29:37,080
Just come clean...

402
00:29:38,010 --> 00:29:39,080
and ask for forgiveness.

403
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:42,150
Why are you turning on me too?

404
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:50,190
This is all your fault, witch.
How dare you frame me?

405
00:29:51,590 --> 00:29:54,030
She's right. This is all a setup.

406
00:29:56,630 --> 00:29:59,340
Fine. If you have proof,
then show it to us.

407
00:29:59,500 --> 00:30:00,570
Here's your proof!

408
00:30:43,310 --> 00:30:46,380
Are things finally about
to go up in flames?

409
00:30:48,890 --> 00:30:51,850
Park Tae Ho, Choi Yu Na,

410
00:30:52,420 --> 00:30:55,020
and everyone at the Adele Group.

411
00:30:57,090 --> 00:31:00,630
I hope they all push each other...

412
00:31:01,430 --> 00:31:03,200
into a fiery pit of despair.

413
00:31:14,980 --> 00:31:18,010
It looks like our key witness
has arrived.

414
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:18,140
(Pearl in Red)

415
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:23,310
Choi Yu Na, how dare you lie to me
and tarnish Adele Group's name?

416
00:32:23,380 --> 00:32:25,250
The Adele Group chairman's wife...

417
00:32:25,250 --> 00:32:26,720
resorting to kidnapping
and imprisonment?

418
00:32:26,780 --> 00:32:28,220
What are you talking about?

419
00:32:28,220 --> 00:32:29,450
I'm telling you, I've been framed.

420
00:32:29,520 --> 00:32:32,390
In my own home?
Right in front of me? The nerve!

421
00:32:32,460 --> 00:32:34,160
Are you really going
to leave it at that?

422
00:32:34,220 --> 00:32:36,530
You're not fixing anything.
You're just covering it up.

423
00:32:36,590 --> 00:32:39,760
They will be punished,
but on my terms.

424
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:43,670
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
